<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
      <h1>L3Harris (LHX)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of L3Harris Technologies — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
      <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })} · Data: stockanalysis.com</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
      <div class="verdict-price">{roundedIV !== null ? `$${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="verdict-vs">
        {currentPrice !== null ? `vs. market price of $${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} (${marginOfSafety}%)` : 'Market price unavailable'}
      </div>
      <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
        {verdictText}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{revenue2025 !== null ? `$${(revenue2025/1000000000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Total Revenue</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{fcfM !== null ? `$${(fcfM/1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{eps !== null ? `$${eps.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">EPS (Trailing)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{operatingMargin !== null ? `${operatingMargin.toFixed(1)}%` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{netCashM !== null ? `$${(netCashM / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
    <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
    <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
        <p>L3Harris generated <strong>{fcfM !== null ? `$${fcfM.toLocaleString()} million` : 'N/A'}</strong> in free cash flow. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything, including capital expenditures required to maintain their defense platforms.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
        <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1*100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects the steady nature of defense contracting, backlog visibility, and margin expansion efforts following the L3 and Harris merger integrations and Aerojet Rocketdyne acquisition.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
        <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal*100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> — slightly below long-term GDP growth. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate).</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
        <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate*100).toFixed(2)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This is based on the 10Y Treasury ({(riskFreeRate*100).toFixed(2)}%) plus an equity risk premium adjusted by the stock's beta ({actualBeta.toFixed(2)}).</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
        <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash ({netCashM !== null ? `$${Math.round(netCashM).toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesM !== null ? `${Math.round(sharesM).toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
    <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
    <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

    <div class="assumption-grid">
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          L3Harris operates in a highly consolidated defense sector with strong pricing power and long-term contracts. The 8% growth assumes moderate top-line expansion driven by global defense budgets, combined with steady margin improvements as recent acquisitions are fully digested.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
        <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Calculated using the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM). 10Y Treasury: {(riskFreeRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%. Equity risk premium: {(equityRiskPremium * 100).toFixed(1)}%. Beta: {actualBeta.toFixed(2)}. This cost of equity accurately reflects the relatively lower volatility of a prime defense contractor.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We conservatively use 2.5% to reflect mature market dynamics in the aerospace and defense industry. A 2.5% terminal rate acknowledges that L3Harris will grow indefinitely alongside standard inflation and sovereign defense spending.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
    <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
