                <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[j] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                  {v !== null ? `$${v}` : 'N/A'}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ WHAT THE MODEL DOESN'T CAPTURE ═══ -->
    <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>

    <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Budget Increases:</strong> Unexpected geopolitical tensions often result in rapid increases in the U.S. defense budget, significantly boosting order backlogs for L3Harris.</li>
      <li><strong>M&A Synergies:</strong> Better-than-expected cost savings from the Aerojet Rocketdyne acquisition or past integrations could expand margins faster than projected.</li>
      <li><strong>Space Systems Boom:</strong> Rapid acceleration in the militarization of space could disproportionately benefit L3Harris's space division.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Defense Budget Cuts:</strong> Any flatlining or reduction in the U.S. Department of Defense budget directly impacts L3Harris's addressable market.</li>
      <li><strong>Supply Chain & Inflation:</strong> Fixed-price contracts can compress margins severely if labor and material costs rise faster than expected.</li>
      <li><strong>Execution Risk:</strong> Integrating large acquisitions (like Aerojet Rocketdyne) carries execution risk; failure to achieve synergies can drag down overall FCF generation.</li>
    </ul>

